25/07/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The Council of Ministers has endorsed a bill that would pave the way for professional soldiers in Serbia-Montenegro's armed forces to participate in UN peacekeeping missions abroad, the government announced in a press statement Friday (23 July). Under the draft law, aimed at meeting Serbia-Montenegro's international obligations as a UN member country, the federal parliament would vote on deployment decisions proposed by the government. (Beta, Serbia-Montenegro government Web site - 23/07/04)
